The phenomenon occurs when the tournament number \( n \) divides the year \( Y(n) = 1978 + n \). This simplifies to \( 1978 \mod n = 0 \), meaning \( n \) must be a divisor of 1978. 

The divisors of 1978 are: \( [1, 2, 23, 43, 46, 86, 989, 1978] \). The divisors greater than 43 (the current tournament number) are \( [46, 86, 989, 1978] \), which gives 4 future occurrences.

\boxed{4}
